I was completely thrown off and it took me twice as long to order since I had to have my topping changed 3 times. When I went to the end to wait for my sandwich, seeing the toppings setup I thought for a minute that I was at Subway but without the part where you say what you want on the sub. I had to actually look around to make sure, and to be honest, since none of the familiar decor was present I wasn't very reassured.  Potbelly's name was nowhere to be seen. Seriously, this was such a generic looking restaurant that even though the food tasted about the same, I left feeling very unsatisfied. Everything that made Potbelly's unique was missing and it's perplexing that this location is trying to blend in with other fast food joints instead of trying to stand out. Don't plan on going back to this location. Will go to ones with the original setup. **** Edited to add: so this response to my review is just as generic as the location.
